					<article id="post-159" class="clearfix post-159 page type-page status-publish hentry" role="article">
						
						<header>							
							<h1>Library Services</h1>
						</header> <!-- end article header -->
					
						<section class="post_content">
							<p>The Library at St. Mary’s provides a wide range of reliable health information resources, including access to many publications and online journals. A full variety of health related databases are also available.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>The <a href="http://healthlibrary.epnet.com/GetContent.aspx?token=6458b32e-dcc1-4a76-8114-20ea8ef8bc65" target="_blank">Online Health Library</a> offers evidence based information.<br />
</strong><br />
<a href="http://healthlibrary.epnet.com/GetContent.aspx?token=6458b32e-dcc1-4a76-8114-20ea8ef8bc65" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter" title="Health Library logo" src="http://www.smgh.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/health_library-logo-300x75.png" alt="Logo for the Health Library feature an illustrated person with hearts arfound them." width="300" height="75" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>For staff &amp; physicians</h2>
<p>The Library’s primary responsibility is to support the needs of staff and physicians. The Library is available 24/7 for staff, physicians and volunteers by using your hospital-issued Identification/Prox Card.</p>
<p><strong>For questions about our Library, contact: </strong><br />
Terry Boshart, Manager of Professional Practice and Patient Safety<br />
519-749-6578 ext. 1406</p>
<h2>For patients &amp; visitors</h2>
<p>While the Library’s primary function is to serve the information needs of our professional staff members, patients and visitors are welcome to browse the collection of fiction in the library, or use the consumer health collection and other resources on site. Patients and visitors are unable to borrow journals or medical publications. You can also make an appointment to see the Librarian (see contact information above).</p>
<p>The Library is located on the 10th floor of the Main Hospital, and is open Monday –Thursday from 8:30 a.m. – 4:30 p.m. If you are not accompanied by a St. Mary’s staff member or volunteer to swipe you in, please knock to gain access to the Library.</p>
<p>Currently, Wi-Fi is not available in the Library, however there are semi-private computer terminals available that provide access to the internet.</p>
<h2>Annual charity book sale</h2>
<p>Are you looking for the perfect vacation novel, quick read, or trying to fill your own personal library? Bookmark your calendar for the Library’s Annual Used Book Sale. Held the last week of October, this annual event raises funds to reinvest in database subscriptions and library resources. All paperback books are $1.00 and hard cover books are $2.00 – a deal that can’t be beat!</p>
													</section> <!-- end article section -->
						
